## API Routes Design

### Authentication

| Method | Route | Auth? | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/auth/google` | No | Initiates Google OAuth flow в†’ redirects to Google |
| `GET` | `/auth/google/callback` | No | Google redirects here with auth code в†’ creates session |
| `POST` | `/auth/logout` | Yes | Destroys session, clears cookie |
| `GET` | `/auth/me` | Yes | Returns current user profile + connected integrations |

### Core API

| Method | Route | Auth? | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/api/inbox` | Yes | Fetches items from all connected integrations. Returns `InboxItem[]` |
| `POST` | `/api/analyze` | Yes | Sends inbox items to Gemini (or returns cached). Returns `AnalysisResult` |
| `GET` | `/api/analyses` | Yes | List past analysis runs (history) |
| `PATCH` | `/api/tasks/:id` | Yes | Update task status (complete/dismiss) |

### Integration Management

| Method | Route | Auth? | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/api/integrations/slack` | Yes | Save Slack bot token (encrypted) |
| `POST` | `/api/integrations/jira` | Yes | Save Jira credentials (encrypted) |
| `DELETE` | `/api/integrations/:provider` | Yes | Disconnect an integration |
| `GET` | `/api/integrations` | Yes | List connected integrations (no tokens in response) |

