## Execution Order

### Phase 1: Infrastructure (P0 Foundation)
1. Create `docker-compose.yml` + `.env.example`
2. Scaffold `server/` with Express + TypeScript
3. Set up PostgreSQL connection + schema + migration runner
4. Set up Redis connection
5. Implement `crypto.service.ts` (AES-256-GCM)
6. Implement Google OAuth flow (routes + controller + service)
7. Implement session middleware + `requireAuth`

### Phase 2: Core Backend (P0 continued)
8. Implement Gmail service (server-side)
9. Implement Calendar service (server-side)
10. Implement Slack service (server-side proxy)
11. Implement Jira service (server-side proxy)
12. Implement inbox aggregation route
13. Implement Gemini service (server-side, with Zod validation)
14. Implement analysis + task routes
15. Implement integration management routes

### Phase 3: Frontend Rewire
16. Create `services/api.ts` (fetch wrapper)
17. Replace LoginScreen with Google Sign-In
18. Update PermissionScreen (remove Google, keep Slack/Jira)
19. Update Dashboard to call backend
20. Update App.tsx with auth state management
21. Update vite.config.ts with proxy

### Phase 4: P1 Hardening
22. Add Redis caching for AI responses
23. Add prompt injection sanitizer
24. Add React Error Boundaries
25. Add mobile responsive breakpoints
26. Add rate limiting middleware

### Phase 5: Docs & Dev Setup
27. Write MIGRATION.md
28. Update README.md
29. Add P2 TODO stubs throughout codebase

