## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please answer these before I start writing code:

### Q1: Database access вЂ” Raw `pg` or Drizzle ORM?
I'm proposing **raw `pg`** with handwritten SQL in typed query functions. This is simpler and gives you full control. But if you prefer **Drizzle ORM** (type-safe query builder, auto migrations), I can use that instead. Which do you prefer?

### Q2: Do you have a Google Cloud project with OAuth credentials?
I need to know if you already have a **Google Cloud Console project** with:
- OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application type)
- Authorized redirect URI set to `http://localhost:3001/auth/google/callback`

If not, I'll include setup instructions in the README.

### Q3: TypeScript on the backend too?
Your frontend is TypeScript. I'm assuming you want the **backend in TypeScript as well** (with `tsx` for dev, `tsc` for build). Confirm?

### Q4: Passport.js or manual OAuth?
You mentioned Passport.js. I actually recommend **manual OAuth** (just `google-auth-library` + direct HTTP calls) for this project because:
- Passport adds middleware abstraction that obscures what's happening
- We only have one provider (Google) for now
- Manual is ~50 lines of code and fully transparent

If you prefer Passport.js for familiarity or future multi-provider support, I'll use it. Your call?

### Q5: Frontend restructure вЂ” move into `src/`?
Currently your React files (App.tsx, index.tsx, components/, services/) sit at the **project root**. This is unusual and will conflict with having `server/` alongside them. I recommend moving all frontend source into a `src/` directory:

```
Before:                    After:
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ App.tsx               в”њв”Ђв”Ђ src/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ index.tsx             в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ App.tsx
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ components/           в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ index.tsx
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ services/             в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ components/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ types.ts              в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ services/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ constants.ts          в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ types.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ server/               в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ constants.ts
                          в”њв”Ђв”Ђ server/
```

This is a clean separation. OK to do this, or do you want to keep the flat structure?

